dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v2.systemtemplate.transportprotocols

Interface IJ1939TpPg

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEntity

    public interface IJ1939TpPg
extends IEntity
    IJ1939TpPg: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    A J1939TpPg represents one J1939 message (parameter group, PG) identified by the PGN (parameter group number) that can be received or transmitted via J1939Tp.

    GENERATED CODE. DO NOT CHANGE!

        Query the value of the attribute Pgn.

        Parameter group number (PGN) of a J1939 message (parameter group, PG) that can be received or transmitted via J1939Tp. The PGN may be omitted when the a directPdu is referenced and is mapped into a CanFrameTriggering with an identifier.

      • getTpSdu

        IIPdu getTpSdu()
        Query the undirectional to-one association TpSdu.

        Reference to IPdus that are segmented by the Transport Protocol. To support the low-level routing of NPdu's the NPdu is a specialization of an IPdu. More details can be found in the NPdu class description. Nevertheless the J1939TpConnection must not reference a NPdu with this tpSdu reference.

        Returns:
        the referenced entity or null
        Throws:
        TresosDBException - in case of an error

      • getSdus

        java.util.Set<? extends IIPdu> getSdus()
        Query the undirectional to-many association Sdu.

        Reference to IPdus that are segmented by the Transport Protocol. If more than one IPdu is referenced, the IPdus are used when the same PGN is received in parallel via different transport protocols (BAM, CMDT, direct) on the same J1939TpConnection.

        the referenced entities
